  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which cream is best for removing dark spots in the face?",
  "response": "The best cream for removing dark spots on the face depends on the cause of the spots, your skin type, and the ingredients that work for you. Here are some popular options backed by dermatologists:\n\n### 1. **Hydroquinone-Based Creams**\n   - **What it does:** A gold standard for treating hyperpigmentation. It lightens dark spots by inhibiting melanin production.\n   - **Examples:** Ambi Fade Cream, Paula's Choice Dark Spot Eraser.\n   - **Note:** Use for short periods (2\u20133 months) and under dermatologist guidance, as prolonged use can cause side effects.\n\n### 2. **Retinoids (Retinol/Tretinoin)**\n   - **What it does:** Promotes skin cell turnover, fades dark spots, and improves skin texture.\n   - **Examples:** Differin Gel, ROC Retinol Correxion Deep Wrinkle Night Cream.\n   - **Note:** Start with a low concentration to avoid irritation, and always use sunscreen.\n\n### 3. **Vitamin C Serums**\n   - **What it does:** Brightens skin, fades dark spots, and protects against free radical damage.\n   - **Examples:** SkinCeuticals C E Ferulic, TruSkin Vitamin C Serum.\n   - **Note:** Pair with sunscreen for best results.\n\n### 4. **Kojic Acid**\n   - **What it does:** Lightens dark spots by inhibiting melanin production.\n   - **Examples:** Kojie San Lightening Soap, Alpha Arbutin + Kojic Acid Serum.\n   - **Note:** May cause irritation for sensitive skin.\n\n### 5. **Alpha Arbutin**\n   - **What it does:** A gentler alternative to hydroquinone that reduces dark spots.\n   - **Examples:** The Ordinary Alpha Arbutin 2% + HA, Axis-Y Dark Spot Correcting Glow Serum.\n\n### 6. **Niacinamide (Vitamin B3)**\n   - **What it does:** Reduces pigmentation, evens skin tone, and improves skin barrier.\n   - **Examples:** CeraVe PM Facial Moisturizing Lotion, Paula's Choice 10% Niacinamide Booster.\n\n### 7. **Azelaic Acid**\n   - **What it does:** Reduces pigmentation, acne, and inflammation.\n   - **Examples:** The Ordinary Azelaic Acid Suspension 10%, Finacea Gel.\n   - **Note:** Suitable for sensitive and acne-prone skin.\n\n### 8. **Licorice Root Extract**\n   - **What it does:** Natural brightening agent that reduces melanin production.\n   - **Examples:** SkinMedica Lytera 2.0 Pigment Correcting Serum.\n\n### Tips for Using Dark Spot Creams:\n- **Patch Test:** Always test a small area to check for irritation.\n- **Sun Protection:** Use a broad-spectrum SPF 30+ daily to prevent further darkening.\n- **Consistency:** Results take time\u2014use consistently for 4\u20136 weeks.\n- **Consult a Dermatologist:** For persistent or severe pigmentation, professional advice is best.\n\nIf you're unsure which product to choose, consult a dermatologist for personalized recommendations.",
